cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with extensions of Linear Temporal Logic (LTL) and its parameterized versions.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses algorithms for solving games, which is a common topic in AI.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the syntax and semantics of a new logic.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with ω-regular properties and their expressiveness in the logic.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses algorithmic properties of the logic.
